WorkItem.Description:
Given the following XAML:
<TextBox Text="Binding Name"/}
<wpftk:DatePicker SelectedDate="{Binding Birthday}" />
 
and bind it to the following view model:
public class PersonViewModel {
  public string Name { get; set; }
  public DateTime Birthday { get; set; }
}
 
The Name property will be synchronized with the view, but the Birthday property will not. If you change the XAML to explicitly specify a TwoWay binding for the DatePicker, the Birthday property is properly synchronized.
 
<wpftk:DatePicker SelectedDate="{Binding Birthday, Mode=TwoWay}" />
 
By default, WPF controls use two-way bindings, which makes MVVM seamless. The DatePicker uses a one-way binding by default. Could the DatePicker please be changed to work like the built-in WPF controls?
